winePairing.pairingText: Cajun works really well with Albarino, Sauvignon Blanc, and rosé Wine. These low-tannin, lower alcohol wines will complement the heat in spicy cajun dishes, instead of making your mouth burn more. One wine you could try is Pazo de Senorans Albarino. It has 4.1 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 20 dollars.
